    "title": "My Evidence-Based Diet - How to Eat Healthy? (and Enjoy it!)",
    "body": "2023/07/03 - In 2018 I was just graduated and unemployed on vacation. Back then I was looking for PhDâ€™s, because to be 100% honest with youâ€¦ I had no idea of what I wanted to do with my life, and PhD seemed a good and productive way to postpone such a decision for a few more years :) I remember until this day: me, at my momâ€™s basement (she is the sweetest, she had prepared a full room just for me to come and live with her for a few months), 2 a. m. in the night, reseraching on my computer how to eat healthy? I stumbled upon MANY different tips, recommendations, doctrines, superstitions and bro-sciencesâ€¦ all of them swearing to be the best when it comes to eating healthyâ€¦ After more than a month compiling pages and pages of information, two things came out as trustworthy and evidence-based enough for me to trust:  a healthy diet provides the minimum of macro- and micro-nutrients through whole foods as much as it is feasible, and a healthy diet contains (near-)zero of scientificaly studied unhealthy foods/nutrients. There are a ton of research online "
